      "content": "wait, did you say metformin? i dont take metformin, i use insulin. and youre saying it's a \"serious risk\" to skip one dose? i've done this before when i was traveling and barely ate and i was fine. honestly it feels like you're being way too cautious. if my levels are stable and i didn't eat carbs, isn't it basically a fact that i don't need the insulin right now? just tell me straight, is it actually dangerous or are you just being extra cautious?",
